Data models in DBMS:-
———————
Def:a data model defines how data is stored,organized and manipulated in a database 

1.physical data model
————
Def:dascribes how data is physically stored in storage devices 
Audience:database administrator 

2.logical data model
———
Defines the structure of data (entities, attributes,relationships)
Independent of physical storage areas.

Audience:developers and data architects 

3.hierachical data model
———
Data is represented as a tree structure (parent child relationships)

Eg:-company—>department—>employees.

4.network data model
———
Data is represented as graph with records(nodes)and relationships (edges)

Eg:-student enrolled in multiple courses, courses teach by multiple professors

5.⁠ ⁠relation data models(RDBMS)

def: data is stored in tables(relations) with rows(tuple) and coloumns(attributes)

eg: student(id,name,marks,dept_id)
departments(dept_id,dept_name)


